}{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 Eleventh Truth: Men Need to be Personalist Feminists}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab Women cannot fully exercise their feminine genius for promoting human dignity when men do not seek \softline
their collaboration or otherwise fail to respect the basic truths about women. Indeed, unless men fully commit to \softline
personalist feminism, they will fail to see the need to be proactive in remedying within themselves and within every \softline
institution all those ways that women are oppressed. They will also fail to see the need to collaborate with women in \softline
the building of the civilization of love.  And this civilization of love cannot be built without the insights of women \softline
who must bring their feminine genius to bear on the problem of structuring institutions to respect the person. Men \softline
must therefore be personalist feminists before the civilization of love can be fully realized.\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab The civilization of love thus requires all to answer the call to personalist feminism and to seek to counter \softline
the gender effects of Original Sin by honoring, at the very least, these basic truths about women: (1) women are the \softline
equals of men; (2) the sexuality of women is designed for spousal oneness with their sexual complements (i.e., men); \softline
(3) women{\u8212\'97}like men{\u8212\'97}achieve fulfillment only through love; (4) women still suffer from male oppression due to \softline
Original Sin; (5) male oppression can be countered only through the love prescribed by the personalistic norm and \softline
embodied in the practice of personalist feminism; (6) personalistic love identifies collaboration to be essential to \softline
human interaction including male/female interaction; (7) personalistic feminism{\u8212\'97}like the Church{\u8212\'97}seeks to \softline
humanize the world; (8-9) maternity{\u8212\'97}whether biological or spiritual{\u8212\'97}is essential to the fulfillment of women; and \softline
(10) men need to become personalist feminists.\par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab Since it is not a kindness to women to disregard her genius in promoting the welfare of others, to kill her \softline
children, to attack her maternity, to refuse to collaborate with her, to reduce her to the status of a sexual object or a \softline
beast of burden, and to fail to love her as an equal.  \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab It is thus not the Church who oppresses women but contemporary culture. \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab \par
}{\plain \fs20 \b\fs20 In Conclusion}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 : \par
}{\plain \fs20 \fs20 \tab Since all are called to a collaborative and providential love that is eager to oppose evil whenever and \softline
